      "role": "user",
      "content": "proprietary algorithms? that sounds a bit suspicious. if it's just a dynamic buffer for spikes, why is it sitting at a constant 20% loss right now while my usage is actually low? and if it's for my benefit, why aren't the logs showing 'reserved for spike protection'? they're just showing it as 'unallocated/internal system overhead'. \n\nlook, if this is a technical glitch or some background process eating my credits, just tell me. i'd rather have an honest answer than some vague talk about predictive analytics. is there something else running on this node?",
